---

<Base
  title="Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy in Houston, Texas | The Oaks Plastic Surgery"
  description="Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy in Houston, Texas at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Board-certified plastic surgeons offering personalized care."
  headerTitle="Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy in Houston, Texas"
  headerImage="/img/back-lift-hero.jpg"
  headerMarginBottom={60}
  canonical="https://theoaksplasticsurgery.com/lipectomy-houston"
>
<section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp lead text-center">
                                A Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy helps remove excess skin and fat from the back, love handles, and saddle bag area.  This procedure is most commonly performed after massive weight loss.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <h2 class="wow fadeInUp center text-center"> </h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Why to have a Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in Houston, Texas? </h3>
                                <p>
                                    Many of our patients at The Oaks Plastic Surgery who have undergone massive weight loss or have developed excess back skin or love handles with age are very self-conscious about this area.  They complain that clothes don’t fit correctly and are bothered by excess skin rolls.  Patients also have problems with excess moisture under the skin which causes hygiene issues,.  A Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy helps lift and suspend the lower body to recreate curves and get rid of the excess skin and rolls present even after significant weight loss.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    A Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy procedure is often a careful balance between scarring and contour.  While everyone’s goal is to maximize contour and minimize scarring, sometimes a trade off must exist. At The Oaks Plastic Surgery we take care to place the scar low so that it could be hidden in underwear and pants.  The plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery want to work with you to achieve your specific goals.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>If you are interested in an  Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy in Houston, Texas</h3>
                                <p>
                                    You can schedule an appointment can be made with Dr. Danielle Andry or Dr. Nandi Wijay.  You can expect the initial consultation to last an hour or more. In your consultation, your TOPS plastic surgeon will:
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Listen to your specific complaints and goals  </li>
                                    <li>Perform a thorough examination, focusing on your individual anatomy and measurements</li>
                                    <li>Discuss recommendations regarding surgical or nonsurgical techniques that may help you achieve your goals</li>
                                    <li>If a Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy is the right option for you, Dr. Danielle Andry or Dr. Nandi Wijay will discuss the details of the plastic surgery procedures that are offered and which approach is right for you </li>
                                    <li>Preoperative photographs will be taken and the cosmetic surgical plan will be analyzed for you with the use of your photographs </li>
                                    <li>The risks and benefits of surgery will be thoroughly outlined for you</li>
                                    <li>You will be given ample opportunity to ask questions from our physicians and staff regarding the Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy and any other surgical or nonsurgical procedures you may be interested in</li>
                                    <li>You will be sent home with a packet of information regarding the procedure including a detailed consent form and instructions for before and after the Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy</li>
                                </ul>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect the day of your Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy procedure?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    The day of your surgery, your TOPS plastic surgeon will meet you in the preoperative area to go over any last minute questions or concerns you may have.  They will make preoperative markings and will perform extensive checks and attention to detail ensuring high quality care and safety.  You will meet the anesthesiologist and their team, as well as the members of our plastic  surgery operative team.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    During your cosmetic procedure, our TOPS plastic surgeons pay meticulous attention to detail and work as a team to ensure a great result with a focus on safety and quality.  Your family will be updated of your status periodically and will be able to talk with the plastic surgeon one-on-one after the procedure is completed.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What procedures are often performed along with a Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy? </h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Many patients seeking Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy have undergone massive weight loss and require removal of excess skin from several areas of the body including the arms, abdomen, thighs, breast, and face.  Additionally, many of these patients have lost volume in their buttocks and breast area, leaving them saggy and deflated.  The most common surgeries performed along with Lower Body Lift/Belt Lipectomy are abdominoplasty, liposuction, breast lift (with or without breast augmentation using a breast implant or fat grafting), brachioplasty  (arm lift), thighplasty (thigh lift), upper bra line back lift, and buttocks augmentation.  Dr. Danielle Andry or Dr. Nandi Wijay spend a large part of their training working with one of the innovators in body contouring surgery after massive weight loss. They have experience in both staging and combining many of these massive weight loss body contouring procedures and can counsel their patients on the timing and progression of these surgeries.   Please visit our <a href="/coming-soon">massive weight loss/body</a> contouring page for more details.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
